<p><a href="http://www.mathcs.sjsu.edu/faculty/rucker/">Rudy Rucker the Elder</a>, writer, mathematician, and computer scientist, is one of the great, weird, untamed minds of contemporary science fiction. He has written <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/redirect?link_code=ur2&tag=theinfinitema-20&camp=1789&creative=9325&path=external-search%3Fsearch-type=ss%26keyword=Rudy%20Rucker%26index=books">dozens of books</a><img src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=theinfinitema-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" width="1" height="1" border="0" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" />, and people with ears may be interested in the music/voice CD <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B000000R3W/theinfinitema-20/104-1458931-9501560?%5Fencoding=UTF8&camp=1789&link%5Fcode=xm2">Like a Passing River</a>, based on his almost-unobtainable memoir <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0938075675/104-1458931-9501560?camp=1789&link%5Fcode=xm2&n=283155">All the Visions</a> and performed by the American Baroque Ensemble. You can also pique your Rudy curiosity with <a href="http://www.rudyrucker.com/pdf/interviewsposted.pdf">high-volume Rudy-interviews</a> available in pdf, and drink from <a href="http://www.mathcs.sjsu.edu/faculty/rucker/writerstoolkit.pdf">
fractal writerly advice</a>, useful and gnarly, that will doubtless do you good.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.rudyrucker.com/little.html">Rudy Rucker the Younger</a>, although he had no apparent part in this story, is also a force to be reckoned with. The two Rudys produced the ineffably wonderful Ruckeresque fiction <a href="jenna_and_me.html">Jenna and Me</a> for the Infinite Matrix in 2003. We also published an excerpt from the elder Rudy's novel <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0007UDZ28/ref=ase_theinfinitema-20/104-1458931-9501560?s=books&v=glance&n=283155&tagActionCode=theinfinitema-20">Spaceland</a> in 2002, of which there is nothing left on site but a <a href="../excerpts/spaceland1.html">spicy illustration</a> by his friend Paul Mavrides. Enjoy.</p>
